Urgent : U.S. : Iraqi Promise Unacceptable
WASHINGTON , November 14 ( Xinhua ) -- U.S. National Security Adviser Sandy Berger said that Iraq 's promise to cooperate with U.N. weapons inspectors was " unacceptable . "
Earlier , U.S. President Bill Clinton decided to stay home to deal with the Iraqi crisis and let Vice President Al Gore to replace him to attend the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation ( APEC ) meeting .
